               <head>Poetry of Fayyaz Lahiji, 6 items (a-f)</head>
               <msContents class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh85129656 https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2004001838">
                  <summary>Collection of poetic compositions in varied forms and genres by the Qumm-trained Shīʿī theologian at the court of Shāh ʿAbbās II Ṣafavī (r. 1052-1077/1642-1667), Ḥakīm Mullā ʿAbd al-Razzāq ibn ʿAlī ibn Ḥusayn Lāhijī, author of the 
            <title>Gawhar-i murād</title>, who took the takhalluṣ Fayyāz̤ (d. 1072/1661). Volume not dated; datable from the mid to late seventeenth century. Neat to rough scribal nastaʿlīq-i khafī; occasional rubrication in rough nastaʿlīq probably supplied by a later hand. Limited annotations and corrections in margins. Intermittent pencil foliation. Lacking original binding. Paper dust wrapper (BEIC legal publication on Regulation XVII for September 1817); partial watermarks (S &amp; C Wise, 1814); labels, torn and stained. Folios unbound; cropped, water and fungal stains, extensive wormholes, later repairs. Condition fragile.
                  </summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1373-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="3v">ff. 1v-3v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1373a.</p>
                        <p>Untitled preface or dībāchah in refined prose commencing this volume of poems by the poet Fayyāz̤ (d. 1072/1661), indicating the text was composed in India.</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656389.0x000001 viaf_16145304708378611094">Fayyāz̤</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656389.0x000001 viaf_16145304708378611094">فيّاض</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1373-item2">
                     <locus from="4r" to="101v">ff. 4r-101v</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_16145304708378611094">Fayyāz̤</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_16145304708378611094">فيّاض</persName>
                     </author>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1373b.</p>
                        <p>Untitled collection of eulogies or qaṣāʾid, with rubrics, by the poet Fayyāz̤ (d. 1072/1661).</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1373-item3">
                     <locus from="101v" to="130r">ff. 101v-130r</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_16145304708378611094">Fayyāz̤</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_16145304708378611094">فيّاض</persName>
                     </author>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1373c.</p>
                        <p>Untitled collection of muqaṭṭaʿāt, tarkībāt, and tarjīʿāt (including haftband), with intermittent rubrics, by the poet Fayyāz̤ (d. 1072/1661).</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="4" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1373-item4">
                     <locus from="131r" to="299r">ff. 131r-299r</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_16145304708378611094">Fayyāz̤</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_16145304708378611094">فيّاض</persName>
                     </author>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1373d.</p>
                        <p>Untitled collection of lyrics or ghazalīyāt (usually theological, mystical, or courtly in theme), in alphabetic order, by the poet Fayyāz̤ (d. 1072/1661).</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="5" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1373-item5">
